docs.lead_paragraph: BUENOS AIRES, June 6. -- Rivalry between the peacemakers has further slowed the Chaco peace negotiations. It was intimated tonight in circles close to the mediators that little more could be done until the Chilean Foreign Minister, Miguel Cruchaga Tocornal, arrived in response to an invitation that Foreign Minister Carlos Saavedra Lamas of Argentina sent to the Foreign Ministers of all the mediating nations.

headline.main: RIVALRIES IMPEDE CHACO PEACE TALKS; Negotiations at Buenos Aires Await Arrival of Chilean Foreign Minister.

docs.lead_paragraph: IT is a terrible tale that Mme. Dombrowski unfolds, this history of Paraguay in the Eighteen Sixties. Many of the characters seem bizarre, unbelievable, yet the main events of the story are solid facts of history. Don Jose Gaspar Tomas Rodriguez de Francia was the son of a mule driver, a Brazilian half-caste who, migrated with his family to Paraguay.

headline.main: A Remarkable South American Historical Novel; LAND OF WOMEN. By Katharina von Dombrowski. 416 pp. Boston: Little, Brown & Co. $2.50.
